==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[nacod]]''
===Adjective===
{{en-adj-notcomp}}
{{WikiSaurus-link|nude}}
# Not wearing any clothes.
#:''She was as '''naked''' as the day she was born.''
# Glib, without decoration, put bluntly.
#:''The '''naked''' truth'', '''''naked''' facts''.
# [[unprotected]]
#: '''''naked''' flame''

